practice.text: People say nothing is impossible, but I do nothing every day.

aaaa.text: Who in the world am I? Ah, that is the great puzzle.

bbbb.text: Begin at the beginning, and go on till you come to the end: then stop.

cccc.text: Why, sometimes I've believed as many as six impossible things before breakfast.

dddd.text: It is no use going back to yesterday, because I was a different person then.

115bc250d5d7.text: Yes, that's it! Said the Hatter with a sigh, it is always tea time.

c9aaea805d0e.text: It would be so nice if something made sense for a change.

7084692c11f7.text: If you don't know where you are going any road can take you there.

cf5d2dedf76a.text: I give myself very good advice, but I very seldom follow it.

2dc1419f1d40.text: Was I the same when I got up this morning?

fe2cf6d02621.text: I knew who I was this morning, but I've changed a few times since then.

1f73769a8a05.text: Now I growl when I'm pleased, and wag my tail when I'm angry.

f026c6e1e9ad.text: I'm never sure what I'm going to be, from one minute to another.

88aa05b6bcb9.text: And what is the use of a book without pictures or conversation?

f4339c57b045.text: Well, I never heard it before, but it sounds uncommon nonsense.
